Police said on Twitter that &quot;a number of people&quot; had died with 31 people injured, some of them seriously. BERLIN - Many people were killed when a coach burst into flames after colliding with a lorry on a motorway in the German state of Bavaria on Monday, the German government said.&quot;Unfortunately numerous people - a tour group from (the eastern German state of) Saxony - lost their lives in this burning bus,&quot; government spokesperson Steffen Seibert told a news conference.A local newspaper, Frankenpost, said that 17 people had been killed, without identifying its source for the information.Police said on Twitter that &quot;a number of people&quot; had died with 31 people injured, some of them seriously.Police said there had been 48 people on the bus at the time of the crash.